[[Vice admiral]] '''Cristóbal Colón de Carvajal y Gorosábel, 18th Duke of Veragua, 17th Duke of la Vega, 19th Marquess of Aguilafuente, 16th Marquess of Jamaica''', [[Grandee|GE]], [[Order of Isabella the Catholic|OIC]] (October 4, 1949 - ) is a Spanish nobleman, businessman and formerly an officer, helicopter pilot, and commander of a naval vessel in the [[Spanish Navy]]. He is a direct descendant of [[Christopher Columbus]] by way of Christopher's son, [[Diego Columbus|Diego]]. From Diego, Colón de Carvajal also holds the [[Duchy of Veragua]] since 1986. As the Duchy corresponds to the present-day [[Veraguas Province]] of the independent republic of [[Panama]], Colón de Carvajal maintains close connections with Panamanian society, and serves on the advisory board of Petaquilla Minerals, a mining company.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.petaquilla.com/newsrelease.aspx?petaquilla=Don%20Cristobal%20Colon%20de%20Carvajal%20Joins%20Advisory%20Board%20of%20Petaquilla%20Minerals%20Ltd|title = Don Cristobal Colon de Carvajal Joins Advisory Board of Petaquilla Minerals Ltd.|date = May 10, 2012|publisher = Petaquilla Minerals Ltd.}}</ref>

In 1986, Colón inherited from his father the [[Cristóbal Colón de Carvajal, 17th Duke of Veragua|17th Duke of Veragua]] all of his titles after he was murdered by [[Basque people|Basque]] nationalist terrorist group [[Euskadi Ta Askatasuna|ETA]].

In 2011, his additional title as [[Duchy of Vega|Duke of Vega]] was among many to be spun away to different recipients, with the new Duke of Vega being Colón's son, [[Ángel Santiago Colón de Mandalúniz]]<ref>[http://titulosnobleza.blogspot.com/2011/04/nuevas-concesiones-de-titulos.html Nuevas Concesiones de Títulos Nobiliarios], [[Blog]] ''Títulos Nobiliarios''</ref><ref>[http://www.boe.es/boe/dias/2011/04/20/pdfs/BOE-A-2011-7102.pdf Real Carta de Sucesión]</ref>

In 1992, to commemorate the 500th anniversary of Columbus' landing on [[Hispaniola]], Colón de Carvajal was co-designated [[Grand Marshal of the Tournament of Roses Parade|Grand Marshal]] of the [[Tournament of Roses Parade]], alongside US Congressman [[Ben Nighthorse Campbell]].

